- **Solution**: `FitnessGoalCards` component shows tracked tasks with today's progress (value, target, % bar) at top of Goals view. Uses cached fitness data — no extra API calls.
- **Completed Date**: 2026-03-31

### GINT-007: Google Contacts — Sync & Events
- **Status**: ✅ Completed (core sync + birthday events + typeahead; two-way write-back pending)
- **Priority**: 🟡 Medium
- **Files**: `src/integrations/google/services/ContactsService.ts`, `src/integrations/google/services/ContactEventsService.ts`, `src/integrations/google/hooks/useGoogleContacts.ts`, `src/components/ContactTypeahead.tsx`, `src/components/GoogleServicesSection.tsx`
- **Issue**: No contact integration existed.
- **Solution**: Full/delta sync from Google People API → `myday_contacts` with syncToken support. Auto-create birthday/anniversary calendar events (skips duplicates). Reusable `ContactTypeahead` component for any form. "Sync Now" and "Create Birthday Events" buttons in IntegrationsView.
- **Completed Date**: 2026-03-31
- **Notes**: Two-way sync (writing notes/tags back to Google) deferred to a later iteration.

### GINT-008: Google Takeout Import (Keep Notes)
- **Status**: ✅ Completed
- **Priority**: 🟢 Low
- **Files**: `src/integrations/google/services/TakeoutImportService.ts`, `src/components/TakeoutImportPanel.tsx`, `src/components/GoogleServicesSection.tsx`
- **Issue**: Users with Google Keep data have no migration path.
- **Solution**: Upload .json files from Google Takeout (Keep export). Preview table shows all notes with title, tags, body preview. User toggles each item to "Task" or "Journal" destination. Bulk set buttons. Skip archived/trashed by default. De-duplicate on re-import using content hash. Replaces "Coming Soon" badge.
- **Completed Date**: 2026-03-31
- **Notes**: .zip direct parsing removed to avoid JSZip dependency — user extracts and uploads .json files.

### GINT-009: IntegrationsView — Google Services Section
- **Status**: ✅ Completed
- **Priority**: 🟡 Medium
- **Files**: `src/components/GoogleServicesSection.tsx`, `src/IntegrationsView.tsx`
- **Issue**: No UI for managing Google service connections.
- **Solution**: Expandable "Google Services" section with cards for Fit, Contacts, and Takeout Import. Connect/Disconnect buttons, status badges, last-synced timestamps.
- **Completed Date**: 2026-03-26

### GINT-010: Tracked Tasks (Auto-Complete from Fitness Data)
- **Status**: ✅ Completed
- **Priority**: 🔴 Critical
- **Files**: `src/types.ts` (TrackedMetric), `src/storage/tasks.ts`, `src/ConfigureView.tsx`, `src/integrations/google/services/TrackedTaskEngine.ts`, `src/hooks/useTrackedTaskSync.ts`, `src/integrations/google/hooks/useGoogleFit.ts`, `supabase/migrations/20260331_task_tracked_metric.sql`
- **Issue**: No way to create tasks that auto-complete based on real data (e.g. "Walk 10K steps").
- **Solution**: Added `TrackedMetric` type (type, target, unit, autoComplete). UI in ConfigureView lets users pick metric (steps/calories/active minutes/distance) and target. `TrackedTaskEngine` runs on every Fit sync and on app startup (via `useTrackedTaskSync`), checking cached fitness data against targets and auto-completing when met. **Backfill support**: if user syncs steps 3-4 days late, earlier tasks get retroactively completed. Manual completion still works alongside auto. Badge on task cards shows target.
- **Completed Date**: 2026-03-31

